RACE.RACE_TEXT: WOODBINE RACE 1 7F All Weather Track CR: 65. Maiden Claiming Purse 36300. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 121 lbs. Claiming Price $15,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: UNDER BUDGET was unhurried having one runner beaten down the backside, improved up the fence around the turn, had clear run on the rail gaining on the leaders in upper stretch, shifted just outside to burst between foes at the sixteenth pole and edged away for the win at the line. SISTER COUSIN took command from the start, was headed outside at the quarter pole, quickly put away the early challenger, opened up mildly at the top of the stretch and gave way to the winner a few strides before the finish line. SILENT PATSY chased behind the frontrunner on the rail in the turn, shifted outside in the thee path getting closer at the quarter pole, was in the hunt between horses in the four path at the top of the stretch and gamely battled to the wire just missing out on getting up for the place share at the wire. MADAM GWEN was three deep outside foes in the middle of the pack down the backstretch, was roused three wide midturn keeping pace with rivals, swung out widest in the six path straightening out for home and showed a good late run rallying in the final sixteenth to close in to be on the fringes in the end. CITRINA travelled in midfield on the rail at the half, made a mild run with rivals on either side midway around the oval and ran evenly on the fence down the stretch to the wire. LADIES RUM settled in mid-pack between horses down the backside, took closer order three wide at the three eighths marker, continued three wide inching closer to the leader throughout the turn, was five wide at the top of the stretch mix of things but stalled in the final sixteenth. WORKING HOLIDAY chased the pacesetter on the outside down the back straight, bid for the lead outside in the two path at the quarter pole, was repelled by the frontrunner turning for home and flattened out in mid-stretch. GOOD BYE NEW YORK stalked near the rear on the outside, made little headway running four wide through the turn and could not be a factor down the lane. TEXENSIS was void of speed trailing down the backside, could not catch up to others running around the bend and was not involved in the stretch drive.

Claiming Price $5,000, if for $4,500, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: NORTHERN RUBY watched the front threesome on the rail down the backstretch, patiently waited for her cue to go running through the turn, shifted out to the three path straightening out foe the drive and wore down the leaders by the sixteenth pole for the lead, clearing away when crossing the finish line. RIFLING veered out at the start, tracked in the second flight on the outside down the back straight, made little gain on the turn, angled four wide at the top of the stretch and closed in smartly to capture the second money just before the wire. VALLEY GIRL stumbled badly at the start, recovered to emerge with a slim lead on the fence at the half mile marker, continued up front with only mild pressure from the outside around the bend and just missed holding for the place share when fading late in deep stretch. TAYLORMOON was part of the trio up front with the other two leaders on each side at the half, reined back a touch to nestle behind the frontrunner through the turn, found a seam in the two path between horses making a bid in upper stretch but needed more late and was outfinished in deep stretch settling for a minor role in the end. SPANISH BEAUTY was allowed to settle near the back outside horses down the backside, made little impact when urged three wide in midturn, angled out to be five wide straightening to the wire and finished up willingly passing foes down the lane. SPARKLE SAMMY prompted the pace three wide outside at the half, chased the pacesetter through the turn, was in range if good enough in the three path at the top of the lane, could not go on late and faded between foes at the furlong marker. GORMLEY GIRL stalked near the rear on the rail in the early going, could not close the gap on rivals around the bend and was not a presence in the stretch run. REINS OF PURPLE was in tight soon after the start, pinched back to trail down the backside, caught up to the field by the quarter pole outside rivals but had little to give driving to the finish line. TIS A PITY settled in mid-pack with runners on either side down the back straight, lost position throughout the turn, swung outside six wide for the drive but came up empty in the stretch run.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: TAKE CHANCES galloped along trailing the field down the backside, made a good rally weaving between runners three wide at the quarter pole, shifted just outside four wide when losing her path at the furlong marker and found more to surge past for the win in deep stretch. HIGH TREASON stalked near the rear on the rail in the early stages, advanced smartly inside at the half, had nowhere to go when stuck behind the tiring early leader at the quarter pole, shifted out to the four path at the top of the stretch and was full of run late but could not get to the winner at the finish line. FOREVER DANISH pressed the pace outside through the first turn, hounded the pacesetter down the back straight on the outside, assumed command three furlongs out, was desperately clinging to the lead on the fence in mid-stretch and retreated while not switching leads in the final furlong. I'M PHANTOM was hustled on the rail to take this field into the first turn, continued up front down the backside, was collared outside with three eighths to go, offered no resistance, backed away on the fence through the far turn, galloped across the finish line and walked home.

SILVER SMOKE took control while in hand on the rail into the first turn, set the fractions down the backside with only mild pressure being asserted from the outside, opened up on the field turning for home, could not find more in reserve to fend off the winner in deep stretch and easily bested the rest for second money at the finish. GUARD OF HONOUR tracked the front pair on the rail down the backside, was urged for more on the fence through the far turn, could not quicken with others at the quarter pole, giving way and was not persevered with in the final furlong.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: SEATTLE SIGNAL brushed inside rival on the start, had a narrow advantage while hounded inside down the backstretch, spurted away comfortably from the chasing rivals at the three furlong marker and was kept to the task holding safe for the convincing score at the finish line. GUNNAWIN was inside foes stalking in the middle of this strung out field at the half mile marker, improved when scrubbed on for more on the rail three eighths from home, shifted outside with momentum at the quarter pole and finished with good energy in the five path down the stretch to close in and capture third when all was said and done.
